review_blob: From a can, of all things...perfect color, and cloudiness for style. No adjunct at all....Pours tight three finger head, but dissipates quicker than Munich styles. Munich style nose and taste. Im picky since I lived and traveled there. Cant believe this quality weissbier is available and made in Texas! So few near perfect beers in TX and this is one. Try for yourself.

The best thing about this beer is the color and Naturtrb cloudiness that is exemplar of this style. No head, adjunct filler Budweisery/ Miller Lighty nose carbonation and flavor. Really quite terrible from a bottle poured into a glass. This beer should have banana, clove, and even bubble gum notes to match the style. Should be malty sweet and crisp. Refreshing. You wont find them in this beer, sadly. It was like cloudy Budweiser.

I do wish Americans who make American craft "Oktoberfest" beers would go to the actual Oktoberfest in Munchen. I grew up there, so. If karbach could replicate the color, nose, head, lacing, mouth feel, and flavor of Oktoberfest beers served at Oktoberfest Wiesn theyd really have a winner. This one pours amber (Big 6 I in Munchen pour golden); no head (Big 6 pour 3 finger head); and has the nosing and taste characteristics of Old Milwaukee, Schlitz, and Milwaukees best. I know Karbach can do better because I have tasted their other beer. Karbachtoberfest stands out as an adjunct filler beer. Better than Bud, Miller, Coors.but not by much

From the tap at the brewery, this tastes like a beer I wish i could make at home for standard beer drinking/ cooking. Not really an Oktoberfest, because we dont drink beer like this in Munchen. But for American craft brew this is close to a colonial style necessity beverage. Low carbonation, almost no head or lacing from the tap. 6.0% ABV Sweet and pours amber in color. Much better than the Pedernales Fburg beers. Those taste like Schlitz.

Sweet hay, straw, soft butter cream. When I taste this beer Im transported the the Theresienwiese. To me, its the only beer of this specific style I have had in the US that looks, smells, and tastes identical to the festzelt pours. Great with roast chicken, bread or brezn, obatzda... Pour in a ma and enjoy. Prost!

Had this the first time from their 0,5L bottle this weekend. Purely the finest palate I have experienced in a hefe-weizen naturtrub. Every quality down the list that I expect from a fine weissbier. Poured into an appropriate weissbier glass. Three finger head. Cloudy golden orange color, wonderful signature notes and finish. Superb! 

After many years of living in Germany (twice) I cant believe I am only just now tasting this one. Please give it a try!
